<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3131] Background cleaner has no daemon service after database creation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3131</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a database is booted, the page cache and the container cache are given a daemon service to perform operations in the background. This happens in BaseDataFileFactory.postRecovery(). When a new database is created this code is not executed (presumably because we don&apos;t perform recovery), so its background cleaner remains inactive until the database is rebooted. The background cleaner should be active after the first boot.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12380582">DERBY-3131</key>
